            "content": "# Forecast Overhaul Implementation Plan\n\n> **For agentic workers:** REQUIRED: Use superpowers:subagent-driven-development (if subagents available) or superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan. Steps use checkbox (`- [ ]`) syntax for tracking.\n\n**Goal:** Consolidate 9 independent forecast PRs (2952, 2953, 2955, 2956, 2957, 2958, 2959, 2960, 2961) into a single coherent overhaul of `forecast_posts` that fixes issues #591, #1044, #1113, #1141, #1148, #1155, #1161, #1576, #1605.\n\n**Architecture:** The consolidated change adopts PR 2958's semantic model where `start` is the transaction date and the advance loop uses `next`. This means the current period is included in forecast output. All other fixes (future-start handling, same-date grouping, pre-check predicates, unconditional predicate evaluation) are adapted to this model. The `filter_posts(forecast_while)` handler is also applied to accounts reports (balance).\n\n**Tech Stack:** C++ (Ledger codebase), CMake build, Python test harness\n\n**Issues fixed:**\n- #591: Future-start periodic transactions silently dropped\n- #1044: `from`/`since` in future dropped by forecast\n- #1113: Future `from` and past `until` not handled correctly\n- #1141: Forecast transactions not sorted by date with mixed intervals\n- #1148: Mixed frequencies corrupting running totals\n- #1155: Same-date postings prematurely terminating forecast\n- #1161: `--now` before `from` date drops forecast; stale `end_of_duration` in stabilize\n- #1576: Current period skipped in forecast output\n- #1605: `--forecast-while` predicate not evaluated for balance reports\n\n---\n\n## File Structure\n\n| File | Action | Responsibility |\n|------|--------|---------------|\n| `src/filters.cc` | Modify (lines 1834-1962) | `forecast_posts::add_post()` and `forecast_posts::flush()` rewrite |\n| `src/chain.cc` | Modify (lines 174-181) | Move `filter_posts(forecast_while)` outside `for_accounts_report` guard |\n| `src/times.cc` | Modify (lines 1637+, 1836+) | Implement `add_duration`/`subtract_duration`; fix stabilize Phase 3 |\n| `test/regress/591.test` | Create | Future-start periodic test |\n| `test/regress/1044.test` | Create | Future `from`/`since` test |\n| `test/regress/1113.test` | Create | Future `from` + past `until` test |\n| `test/regress/1141.test` | Create | Mixed-interval sort order test |\n| `test/regress/1148.test` | Create | Mixed-frequency running total test |\n| `test/regress/1155.test` | Create | Same-date predicate grouping test |\n| `test/regress/1161.test` | Create | `--now` before `from` date test |\n| `test/regress/1576.test` | Create | Current-period inclusion test |\n| `test/regress/1605.test` | Create | Balance report forecast-while test |\n| `test/baseline/opt-forecast-basic.test` | Modify | Add current period to expected output |\n| `test/baseline/opt-forecast-while.test` | Modify | Add current period to expected output |\n| `test/baseline/opt-forecast-years.test` | Modify | Add current period to expected output |\n| `test/baseline/opt-forecast_only.test` | Modify | Reorder for correct date sort + current period |\n| `test/regress/D2829FC4.test` | Modify | Reorder for correct date sort + current period |\n| `test/regress/620F0674.test` | Modify | Add current period to expected output |\n| `test/regress/E627C594.test` | Modify | Add current period to expected output |\n| `test/regress/2043.test` | Modify | Add current period to expected output |\n| `test/regress/370-forecast_period_days.test` | Modify | Add current period to expected output |\n| `test/regress/370-forecast_period_weeks.test` | Modify | Add current period to expected output |\n| `test/regress/cov4-forecast-expired.test` | Modify | Adjust for current period |\n| `test/regress/cov9-journal-autoperiod.test` | Modify | Add current period to expected output |\n| `test/regress/coverage-filter-forecast.test` | Modify | Add current period to expected output |\n| `test/regress/coverage-filters-forecast.test` | Modify | Add current period to expected output |\n| `test/regress/coverage-forecast-new.test` | Modify | Add current period to expected output |\n| `test/regress/coverage-forecast.test` | Modify | Add current period to expected output |\n| `test/regress/coverage-wave6-forecast.test` | Modify | Add current period to expected output |\n\n---\n\n## Chunk 1: Core Code Changes\n\n### Task 1: Fix `stabilize()` Phase 3 stale `end_of_duration` (from PR 2961)\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/times.cc:1836-1842`\n\nThis is an independent correctness fix in `date_interval_t::stabilize()`. When Phase 3 clamps `start` to `initial_start`, the previously-computed `end_of_duration` may now be at or before the clamped start. This causes assertion failures for daily periods with a future start date.\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Read the current stabilize Phase 3 code**\n\nThe code at `src/times.cc:1836-1842` currently reads:\n```cpp\n      if (initial_start && (!start || *start < *initial_start)) {\n        // Using the discovered start, find the end of the period\n        resolve_end();\n\n        start = initial_start;\n        DEBUG(\"times.interval\", \"stabilize: start reset to initial start\");\n      }\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Add stale `end_of_duration` recomputation**\n\nReplace the Phase 3 block with:\n```cpp\n      if (initial_start && (!start || *start < *initial_start)) {\n        // Compute end_of_duration from the quantum-aligned start before\n        // clamping, so that weekly/monthly periods keep their natural\n        // period boundary.\n        resolve_end();\n\n        start = initial_start;\n\n        // If end_of_duration (computed from the old start) is no longer\n        // past the clamped start, it is stale and must be recomputed.\n        if (end_of_duration && *end_of_duration <= *start) {\n          end_of_duration = none;\n          next = none;\n          resolve_end();\n        }\n\n        DEBUG(\"times.interval\", \"stabilize: start reset to initial start\");\n      }\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Implement `add_duration` and `subtract_duration` (from PR 2957)**\n\nThese are declared in `src/times.h:717-719` but have no implementation. Add at `src/times.cc` just before the `resolve_end()` method (around line 1643):\n\n```cpp\ndate_t date_interval_t::add_duration(const date_t& date, const date_duration_t& duration) {\n  return duration.add(date);\n}\n\ndate_t date_interval_t::subtract_duration(const date_t& date, const date_duration_t& duration) {\n  return duration.subtract(date);\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Verify build compiles**\n\nRun: `cmake -B build -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Debug -DUSE_PYTHON=OFF -DUSE_GPGME=OFF && make -C build -j$(nproc)`\n\nExpected: Clean build, no errors.\n\n### Task 2: Rewrite `forecast_posts::add_post()` (consolidating PRs 2953, 2957, 2958, 2959, 2961)\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/filters.cc:1834-1852`\n\nThe new `add_post()` adopts PR 2958's model (advance stored interval using `next`, not local copy using `start`) and adds future/expired detection from PRs 2957/2961.\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Replace the `add_post()` method**\n\nReplace lines 1834-1852 of `src/filters.cc` with:\n\n```cpp\n/**\n * Add a periodic posting for forecasting, initializing its interval.\n *\n * Unlike generate_posts::add_post, this override initializes the interval\n * via find_period and advances it past all fully-elapsed historical periods\n * so that only the current and future periods are generated during flush().\n *\n * Handles three cases:\n *  - Normal: period contains CURRENT_DATE -> advance past elapsed periods\n *  - Future: period starts after CURRENT_DATE -> keep as-is for flush()\n *  - Expired: period finished before CURRENT_DATE -> silently drop\n */\nvoid forecast_posts::add_post(const date_interval_t& period, post_t& post) {\n  date_interval_t i(period);\n\n  // Try to initialize and position the interval at CURRENT_DATE.\n  if (!i.start)\n    i.find_period(CURRENT_DATE());\n\n  // If stabilization failed entirely, nothing to forecast.\n  if (!i.start)\n    return;\n\n  // Drop intervals whose finish date is entirely in the past.\n  if (i.finish && CURRENT_DATE() > *i.finish)\n    return;\n\n  generate_posts::add_post(i, post);\n\n  // Advance the stored interval past all fully-elapsed periods, keeping\n  // the period that contains CURRENT_DATE() so the current period's\n  // forecast is included.\n  date_interval_t& stored = pending_posts.back().first;\n  if (!stored.next)\n    stored.stabilize(CURRENT_DATE());\n\n  // For future-start periods (start > CURRENT_DATE), the loop below\n  // is a no-op, which is correct: flush() will emit the first posting\n  // at start (the future from-date).\n  while (stored.next && *stored.next <= CURRENT_DATE())\n    ++stored;\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Verify build compiles**\n\nRun: `make -C build -j$(nproc)`\n\n### Task 3: Rewrite `forecast_posts::flush()` (consolidating PRs 2952, 2955, 2956, 2958, 2960)\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/filters.cc:1854-1962`\n\nThe new `flush()`:\n- Sorts by `start` (which is now the transaction date under PR 2958's model)\n- Groups all same-date postings before evaluating the predicate (PR 2955)\n- Pre-checks date-based predicates before submission to prevent total corruption (PR 2956)\n- Evaluates the predicate unconditionally, not gated on `POST_EXT_MATCHES` (PR 2960)\n- Removes `POST_EXT_VISITED` on predicate failure for accounts reports (PR 2960)\n- Removes unused `posts_list passed` variable\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Replace the `flush()` method**\n\nReplace lines 1854-1962 of `src/filters.cc` with:\n\n```cpp\n/**\n * Generate all forecast postings into the future.\n *\n * Iterates through pending periodic postings, generating synthetic postings\n * in date order.  All postings sharing the same earliest start date are\n * generated as a group before evaluating the continuation predicate.  This\n * prevents a same-date posting that temporarily fails the predicate from\n * permanently removing a periodic transaction.\n *\n * Date-based predicates are pre-checked before submission to the downstream\n * pipeline, preventing out-of-window postings from corrupting the running\n * total in calc_posts.  Value-based predicates are checked after submission\n * (when the running total is available).\n *\n * A periodic posting is removed from consideration when:\n * - Its start date exceeds forecast_years beyond the last generated date, or\n * - Its group's last matching posting fails the continuation predicate, or\n * - Its interval has no more occurrences.\n */\nvoid forecast_posts::flush() {\n  date_t last = CURRENT_DATE();\n\n  // If there are period transactions to apply in a continuing series until\n  // the forecast condition is met, generate those transactions now.  Note\n  // that no matter what, we abandon forecasting beyond the next 5 years.\n  //\n  // It works like this:\n  //\n  // Earlier, in forecast_posts::add_period_xacts, we cut up all the periodic\n  // transactions into their components postings, so that we have N \"periodic\n  // postings\".  For example, if the user had this:\n  //\n  // ~ daily\n  //   Expenses:Food       $10\n  //   Expenses:Auto:Gas   $20\n  // ~ monthly\n  //   Expenses:Food       $100\n  //   Expenses:Auto:Gas   $200\n  //\n  // We now have 4 periodic postings in `pending_posts'.\n  //\n  // Each periodic postings gets its own copy of its parent transaction's\n  // period, which is modified as we go.  This is found in the second member\n  // of the pending_posts_list for each posting.\n  //\n  // The algorithm below works by iterating through the N periodic postings\n  // over and over, until each of them meets the termination criteria for the\n  // forecast and is removed from the set.\n\n  while (pending_posts.size() > 0) {\n    // Find the earliest start date among all pending postings.\n    pending_posts_list::iterator least = pending_posts.begin();\n    for (pending_posts_list::iterator i = ++pending_posts.begin(); i != pending_posts.end(); i++) {\n      assert((*i).first.start);\n      assert((*least).first.start);\n      if (*(*i).first.start < *(*least).first.start)\n        least = i;\n    }\n\n    date_t earliest_date = *(*least).first.start;\n\n    // Collect all pending postings that share this earliest start date,\n    // so they can be generated and evaluated as a group.\n    std::list<pending_posts_list::iterator> same_date;\n    for (pending_posts_list::iterator i = pending_posts.begin(); i != pending_posts.end(); i++) {\n      if (*(*i).first.start == earliest_date)\n        same_date.push_back(i);\n    }\n\n    // Check the 5-year safety limit using the earliest date.\n    if (static_cast<std::size_t>((earliest_date - last).days()) >\n        static_cast<std::size_t>(365U) * forecast_years) {\n      DEBUG(\"filters.forecast\",\n            \"Forecast transaction exceeds \" << forecast_years << \" years beyond today\");\n      for (auto& it : same_date)\n        pending_posts.erase(it);\n      continue;\n    }\n\n    // Generate all postings in this same-date group.\n    bool any_failed = false;\n    for (auto& it : same_date) {\n      post_t& post = *(*it).second;\n      xact_t& xact = temps.create_xact();\n      xact.payee = _(\"Forecast transaction\");\n      xact._date = earliest_date;\n      post_t& temp = temps.copy_post(post, xact);\n\n      DEBUG(\"filters.forecast\", \"Forecast transaction: \" << temp.date() << \" \"\n                                                         << temp.account->fullname() << \" \"\n                                                         << temp.amount);\n\n      // Pre-check the forecast predicate BEFORE submitting the posting\n      // downstream.  For date-based predicates (e.g. 'd<[2016/03/02]'),\n      // this prevents a posting that falls outside the forecast window\n      // from ever reaching calc_posts and corrupting the running total.\n      // For total-based predicates, the total is not yet accumulated so\n      // the check is typically a pass-through; the post-submission\n      // check below handles termination in that case.\n      {\n        bind_scope_t bound_scope(context, temp);\n        if (!pred(bound_scope)) {\n          DEBUG(\"filters.forecast\", \"  fails pre-check of continuation criteria\");\n          any_failed = true;\n          continue;\n        }\n      }\n\n      // Submit the generated posting to the downstream pipeline.\n      item_handler<post_t>::operator()(temp);\n\n      // Post-submission check: evaluate the predicate again now that\n      // calc_posts has updated the running total.  This handles\n      // value-based predicates like \"total < $3500\".\n      // Check unconditionally (not gated on POST_EXT_MATCHES) so that\n      // accounts reports (balance) also evaluate the predicate.\n      {\n        bind_scope_t bound_scope(context, temp);\n        if (!pred(bound_scope)) {\n          DEBUG(\"filters.forecast\", \"  fails post-submission continuation criteria\");\n          // Remove POST_EXT_VISITED so accounts reports don't count\n          // this posting in their totals.\n          if (temp.has_xdata())\n            temp.xdata().drop_flags(POST_EXT_VISITED);\n          any_failed = true;\n        }\n      }\n    }\n\n    // If any posting in the group failed the predicate, remove all\n    // postings in the group from future consideration.\n    if (any_failed) {\n      for (auto& it : same_date)\n        pending_posts.erase(it);\n      continue;\n    }\n\n    // Advance all postings in the group to their next period, removing\n    // any that have exhausted their intervals.\n    for (auto& it : same_date) {\n      ++(*it).first;\n      if (!(*it).first.start) {\n        pending_posts.erase(it);\n      }\n    }\n  }\n\n  item_handler<post_t>::flush();\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Verify build compiles**\n\nRun: `make -C build -j$(nproc)`\n\n### Task 4: Move `filter_posts(forecast_while)` to apply to all report types (from PR 2960)\n\n**Files:**\n- Modi